The Gaslight Anthem-Get Hurt(Deluxe Edition)mp3 320k what we got  Some thing weaker than I thought it was...Get Hurt is the upcoming fifth studio album by American rock band The Gaslight Anthem, scheduled for release in the UK on August 11, 2014, through Virgin EMI and in the United States on August 12, 2014, through Island Records. It is the first full-length studio album since the band's 2012 release, Handwritten, and marks their first album on Island Records, which absorbed the band and its previous label, Mercury Records.

Produced by Mike Crossey and inspired by vocalist and guitarist Brian Fallon's divorce from his wife of ten years, the band was influenced by artists whose albums represented "career shifts".
